  m_Name: Forepaw_Digit4_Phalanx_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Forepaw_Digit4_Phalanx_R
  partName: Forepaw Digit4 Phalanx Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right forepaw digit four phalanx forms part of the skeletal structure of
    the fourth digit within the canine forepaw. This bone contributes to toe flexibility,
    stability, and coordinated paw movement during locomotion and weight-bearing
    activities.
  - Tendons and ligaments attached to the phalanx control flexion and extension of
    the digit while maintaining proper alignment during walking and running. The
    fourth digit assists with traction, balance, and distribution of mechanical forces
    across the paw.
